Standard Operating Procedure: Local Embedding Setup
1. Environment Preparation
It is best practice to use a virtual environment to avoid messing with the system Python on Rocky Linux.
Bash
# Install python-pip if not already present
sudo dnf install python3-pip -y

# Create and activate a virtual environment
python3 -m venv rag-env
source rag-env/bin/activate
2. Install the Library
The sentence-transformers library handles both the logic and the automatic downloading from the HuggingFace Hub.
Bash
pip install -U sentence-transformers
3. Execution & Automatic Download
When you run the script below for the first time, the library checks your local cache (usually ~/.cache/torch/sentence_transformers/). If the model isn't there, it pulls the weights from HuggingFace.
Create a file named embed_test.py:
Python
from sentence_transformers import SentenceTransformer

# 1. Load the model (This triggers the download on the first run)
model = SentenceTransformer('all-MiniLM-L6-v2')

# 2. Define your text
sentences = ["Milvus is a vector database.", "Rocky Linux is a RHEL derivative."]

# 3. Generate the embeddings
embeddings = model.encode(sentences)

# 4. Inspect the output
print(f"Model Dimension: {len(embeddings[0])}")
print(f"Sample Vector (first 5 values): {embeddings[0][:5]}")
4. Verify the "Math" for Milvus
When you run python3 embed_test.py, pay attention to the Model Dimension output.
•	For all-MiniLM-L6-v2, it will be 384.
•	You must use this number when defining the dim parameter in your Milvus collection schema.
________________________________________
Key Technical Notes for Rocky Linux 9
•	Cache Location: The model weights are stored in your home directory by default. If you are working in a restricted or air-gapped environment later, you can manually move these files to the server.
•	CPU vs. GPU: By default, this library will look for a GPU. On a standard Rocky Linux server without an NVIDIA card, it will automatically and safely fall back to using your CPU.
•	Offline Usage: Once the first run is complete and the weights are downloaded, your code no longer requires an internet connection to generate embeddings.

